<<<code>>>: $CODE
<<<explanation>>>: $EXPLANATION.

API: ApplicationInfo.loadIcon
CODE: if(sdk > android.os.Build.VERSION_CODES.HONEYCOMB) {
            preference.setIcon(app.loadIcon(pm));
        }
EXPLANATION: This code snippet is used to set the icon of a preference in a PreferenceActivity. It first checks if the current SDK version is greater than HONEYCOMB (API level 11), which is the minimum required for the setIcon method. If it is, it sets the icon of the preference to the icon of the application. The loadIcon method of the PackageManager is used to get the icon of the application.


A: You can use the setIcon() method of the Preference class to set the icon of the preference.
Here is an example:
Preference preference = new Preference(this);
preference.setTitle(app.activityInfo.loadLabel(pm));

if(Build.VERSION.SDK_INT >= Build.VERSION_CODES.HONEYCOMB) {
    preference.setIcon(app.loadIcon(pm));
}

In this code, we first set the title of the preference using the loadLabel() method of the ActivityInfo class. Then, we check if the SDK version is greater than or equal to HONEYCOMB (API level 11). If it is, we set the icon of the preference using the loadIcon() method of the ApplicationInfo class.
Please note that the setIcon() method is only available from API level 11 onwards. Therefore, we use the Build.VERSION.SDK_INT constant to check the current SDK version and only set the icon if it is greater than or equal to HONEYCOMB.

